The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 DLF bags Rs 6000cr project

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, July 18: DLF Limited today bagged a Rs 6,000-crore project from the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) to design, develop and operate an international convention centre at Dwarka.

 The proposed centre is close to Delhis international airport and will have a built-up area of about 2 million square feet. The cost of the land will be Rs 900 crore.

 The centre will be designed according to international norms. It will be comparable to the Suntec Convention Center, Singapore, a DLF statement said. The company was the lone bidder for the DDA project. It will have a 6.5-lakh-square-feet convention and exhibition complex, a 6.5-lakh-square-feet hotel complex and 3.95-lakh-square-feet commercial complex. 

 The main convention hall will accommodate 12,000 delegates with telescopic seating arrangements. It can be partitioned into many smaller halls. 




